storyInfo: Returning from a mission, Provence meets her newly joined peers. The Catastrophe Messengers detect an omen of impending Catastrophe within the changing weather, and Provence takes it upon herself to warn the people of the wilderness.

attributes.content: 1:35 P.M. \ Clear
Rhodes Island Landship, Cabin No. 3, Medical Bay
Ok, turn around.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Please try to hold still. Don't move your tail either.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: 61.3... Hmm, your tail has grown longer again.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Alright, that's all.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Is the checkup complete?
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Ahh, that tickled so bad! To be honest, I'm really not used to having my tail measured like this every time. It's really hard to keep it from moving.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Your reaction is still manageable, you tend to just twitch a little. The ones that are really hard to handle are those operators who suddenly try to attack you.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Yeah, there are some spots that are more sensitive after all. I've heard there are some races that you can't touch at all.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: It's true.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Ah, time's up. Here, breathe into this.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: (Huff——)
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Done!
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Yep, no issues.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: The results for the blood test will only be out the day after tomorrow, but I'll have the preliminary diagnostic report ready in a moment.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Here, please drink this dissolving agent.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Alright.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: I'm so sorry for always taking up your time. I feel really bad that you have to do so many examinations.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: I know my own body after all, there's really no problem...
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Provence!
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Ehh, y-yes?
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Please don't say such things again. Just look at the examination data from this check-up, all the indicators have fluctuated!
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: You also stayed outside longer than planned this time!
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Rhodes Island is currently deep in the wilderness and there are barely any known nomadic city routes nearby. Who knows how dangerous it is out there?!
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: If we don't take proper precautions, it's extremely dangerous to stay in such a place!
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: My bad, my bad. Please don't get angry at me, okay?
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: There are a few small villages near our route, and I'm a little worried about them...
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: You may be a professional Catastrophe Messenger, but you still have to look out for your own safety!
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: I promise! I guarantee I'll be safe!
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Look, I covered myself up all the way, just like how you taught me. Don't worry, I won't take any chances with my health!
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Hmm...
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Save your worries. The Catastrophe Messengers have their own ways of looking after themselves.
Especially for Messengers independent of any state, the lone wanderers of the wilderness...
attributes.name: Warfarin

attributes.content: I haven't seen many Catastrophe Messengers who could avoid getting infected, but a normal person would have died many times over if thrown into such environments.
attributes.name: Warfarin

attributes.content: On the contrary, these Messengers are still as lively as ever.
attributes.name: Warfarin

attributes.content: Um, was that a compliment?
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: No.
attributes.name: Warfarin

attributes.content: Sorry, what was that?
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Well, you're not wrong. The environments we work in wouldn't be kind to the normal people. But, as long as you get the right training and avoid taking risks, it's actually not so bad.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: A lot of my colleagues work for a single city-state a big company. Keeps them away from the riskiest work and guarantees a nice salary.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Catastrophe Messengers get paid well, with a high bar to entry. The assessment tests are extremely tough.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: I see...
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Speaking of which, the two new operators who've just arrived recently seem to have been recommended here by the Catastrophe Messenger platform. Are they your peers as well, Provence?
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Ah, are you talking about Leonhardt and Tsukinogi?
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Those two are very well-known, actually...
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: I met the both of them before coming for the check-up. I'm glad that Leonhardt seems to be adjusting well.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Oh? You know that long-eared brat?
attributes.name: Warfarin

attributes.content: He worked this little one over so badly she burst into tears. Just ask her about it.
attributes.name: Warfarin

attributes.content: Dr. Warfarin!
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Fine, fine. I've said enough.
attributes.name: Warfarin

attributes.content: Ahahahahaha.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Was it really that funny?
attributes.name: Warfarin

attributes.content: Oh, right. That brat and that heiress from Higashi haven't yet completed their check-ups. Since you know them, do help to call them over.
attributes.name: Warfarin

attributes.content: Haha, sure, no problem!
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: I'll be going then~
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: I'm done eating. Here's my plate, babe.
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: Skinny? What? Everyone my age is like this. I probably look a little skinner since I'm still growing.
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: Yup, I'm getting enough to eat. I'm always here eating your food, aren't I?
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: The fried rice cake today was delicious! And the egg rolls yesterday were really good too! Ah, I have to go. I have training next, so I'll see you later~
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: Phew.
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: The people here are more vivacious than I expected.
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: *Sigh* If I keep eating like this, I'll get fat sooner or later.
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: That doesn't sound too bad. The lady in the cafeteria seems to really like you.
Good afternoon, Leonhardt. Looks like you're doing well.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: I figured you'd be at the cafeteria around this time, luckily you hadn't gone far. I was looking for you.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Good afternoon, Provence. Please don't make fun of me, I've really started to put on weight since I came here. Some of my clothes don't even fit anymore!
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: Why were you looking for me though?
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: Dr. Warfarin wants you for a follow-up examination. Not just you, Tsukinogi too.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: I went to the dance room earlier, but there was no one there. I don't know where Tsukinogi might be...
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Ah, I know where she is.
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: Besides dancing her religious stuff, Tsukinogi also enjoys finding a quiet spot and looking at the scenery. I saw her near the outer layer just now, she might still be there.
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: Ehh... You haven't been at Rhodes Island for long, but you already know so much.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Hehe, I'm always paying attention to what people like, or don't like.
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: Follow me!
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: Accumulating clouds, a light breeze and dissipating fog...
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: Looks like the weather is turning.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: Ah, how lucky. Tsukinogi's still here.
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: Hello~ Tsukinogi.
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: Good afternoon, Tsukinogi!
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Oh? Good afternoon, to the both of you.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: What's going on? Were you looking for me?
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: Ah, yes. Dr. Warfarin told me to ask you to head to Medical, for a follow-up examination.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Is that so? Alright, I shall head over now.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: Oh, it's not that urgent. I think the medics should be off for lunch now. If you take your time you'll still make it.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: That's right! The ladies of the Medical Department need their break. Let's take the chance to relax as well.
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: Have you had lunch yet, Tsukinogi? The cafeteria here is really good. I highly recommend the fried rice cakes and North Sadleir vegetable stew.
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: Hehe, I've already eaten.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: However, I will have to try out those dishes next time, since you recommended them so highly.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: They will definitely live up to your expectations!
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: Hmm... The scenery here is really nice. I've never really paid attention to this spot before. Didn't expect there was such a place on the landship.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Tsukinogi is really amazing, the same Catastrophe Patrol of Higashi I've heard about.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: You flatter me. I was just looking for a quiet spot.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: Dancing together with everyone is enjoyable, of course, but sitting here quietly and looking at the scenery is also quite pleasant.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: As Catastrophe Messengers ourselves, we also carry the duty of monitoring the environment while we are stationed on the landship. As such, this wouldn't be considered slacking off.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: How dedicated. I really have a lot to learn from my more experienced colleagues.
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: It's our job after all. Ahh, I always end up unconsciously relaxing whenever I'm on the landship...
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: (What's going on? It feels like the weather's changed.)
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: (Why would the tops of the clouds look like that...? They were fine when I came back this morning...)
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: (And the wind marks... The wind isn't blowing strongly, yet it's leaving such distinctive marks...)
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Tsukinogi, look at the clouds over there...
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: This phenomenon, these traits, could it be...
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Blazing yet imperceptible. The fog has dispersed and a gale is building.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: I wasn't completely sure just now, however it seems that we are indeed unfortunate.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: The wind has changed——It's a Regional Catastrophe Outbreak!
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: I'll head out to check!
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: Watch out! A strong wind should be picking up soon, if you head out now you might get blown away!
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Don't worry!
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: ——Such a piddling breeze won't do anything to me!
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: Ahh... What an energetic young man.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: The darker clouds further beyond have started to spread. Based on the moisture in the air and the changing of the wind... Yes, I'm not wrong.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: These are the omens of an incoming Catastrophe.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: How unlucky. To think that we'd encounter a sudden Catastrophe like this.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: When Leonhardt gets back, we need to quickly inform Amiya and the people at the bridge! Thank goodness we discovered it early. We should still have enough time to change directions.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Luckily there aren't any nomadic cities that we need to inform around here.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Nomadic cities usually don't stay in regions with unstable weather like this.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: After all, if they encountered an emergency situation that escalated rapidly like this, the larger nomadic cities wouldn't be able to maneuver in time. The big shots in the cities would never take a risk like that.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: On the other hand, something like Rhodes Island would have no issues avoiding Catastrophes in such situations.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: Ehh, wait a minute... Oh no, oh no!
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Around here... I remember there are a few villages in that direction!
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Huh... Is that true? There are people living on such desolate land?
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: Of course it's true!
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: There are quite a number of villages in the wilderness. It's the same in every country.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: They can't properly enter the nomadic cities, and the arable land around the cities is usually already claimed, so they have no choice but to settle somewhere further and live their lives taking one day at a time.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Since they don't really have a choice, everyone's always prepared to move at any time. All their belongings can be packed up quickly. There's not many people in each village, so they can usually escape to safety given some advance notice.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Oh, now that you mention it, I've heard of similar situations in Higashi.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: Ah... Such things happen everywhere. Even so, no matter how much you get used to it, there is always a chance that you don't make it.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: That's why I always try to make as many detours as possible, to warn these villages...
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: (I wonder if the villagers have noticed the changing weather.)
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: (If not...)
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Sorry to keep you waiting!
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: I had a look at it, and it doesn't bode well.
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: The transformation of the cloud layer is happening very quickly, even the wind has changed. I don't expect this place to remain safe much longer, it'll be a few hours to half a day at most.
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: That fast?!
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: At that speed, the abnormal weather effects will occur all around us soon. We can't go outside like that anymore, it's too dangerous.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: Don't worry, I know. I traveled a short distance towards the Catastrophe just now and didn't see any cities nearby.
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: It'd have been dangerous if I continued forward even if I was adequately prepared, so we're unable to gather any more information for now.
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: Ah, I'll tell you the rest later. Let me report to Amiya first.
attributes.name: Leonhardt

attributes.content: Well then, we'll go and make our own preparations.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: No, I have to go to the villages! I won't be able to sleep at night if I don't!
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Tsukinogi, I'll leave the preparations for the landship to you!
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Hey, wait! Provence, I told you it's too dangerous!
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: Times like this, when we don't know how quickly the Catastrophe will form, even someone of your skill will be in great danger if you go too deep!
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: I... I will be very careful. Someone has to go and warn them!
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: The large nomadic cities have their own Catastrophe Messengers, they'd be fine without us.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: But these small villages and settlements are different!
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: If we don't go, the people out there will probably get caught out.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: A sudden Catastrophe like this could easily catch them off guard long before they could get clear!
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Even so...
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: Isn't our job to provide early warnings and do our best to mitigate the dangers brought about by the Catastrophes?
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: They talk about Catastrophe Messengers like we get paid well and live nice, steady lives, but that's not me!
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: I've never forgotten my purpose.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: 'It's all about saving lives. More lives.'
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Maybe we all have our own ideas about that sentence.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: But to me...
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: To me, it means that whether it's the rich nobles living in the city, or the poor farmers living in the villages, all life is equally important. There is no distinction between lives.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Haha, alright. I understand you.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: Equality of life does mean that one's life cannot be valued in terms of wealth or status...
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: That's a good philosophy.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: Then...!
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: However.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: What about your own life, Provence?
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: Huh? I...
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: To me, these equal lives also include yours.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: Should I just let you put yourself in danger? Only to save more lives?
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: Would you then weigh the value of lives in terms of numbers, and sacrifice the few to save the many?
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: ...I wouldn't say so. If something can only be done by sacrificing lives, then there must be something intrinsically wrong with it.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: But that has nothing to do with our situation! It's not the time to be discussing that either!
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: I know people have a Catastrophe bearing down on them, I have to go and warn them. It's my duty!
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: I won't stop you.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: After understanding your viewpoint, it'd be wrong of me to stop you.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: That's good——
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Yes, I won't stop you. I will go with you.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: Huh?
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Oh, did you forget? I'm a Catastrophe Messenger too. It's only natural for me to go with you.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: But... It will really be dangerous...
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: I'm aware. That's why I have a request to make of you.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: If I determine that the situation is too dangerous, I will stop you even if I have to use force.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: Is that acceptable?
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: That...
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: I only hope that you can value your own life more.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: Thank you.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: I understand. We'll do that then. Let's go!
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: How should I put this... You're very different from how I imagined.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: I thought that an heiress from Higashi would be more... Umm, elitist and snobbish.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Oh? That's a complete misunderstanding.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: I've always been trying my best to grow closer to everyone at Rhodes Island. I've even started to reach saturation lately.
attributes.name: Tsukinogi

attributes.content: Saturation...? That sounds weird...
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: Whatever! Anyway, let's move! If we don't go now, we'll never make it in time!
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: *Sigh* I'll definitely get chewed out by that girl in Medical again when I get back.
attributes.name: Provence

attributes.content: ...Yeah, I'd better come up with my apology first.
attributes.name: Provence
